#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:2
msgid "Xpath注入"
msgstr "XPath Injection"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:5
msgid "Xpath定义"
msgstr "XPath Definition"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:6
msgid ""
"XPath注入攻击是指利用XPath解析器的松散输入和容错特性，能够在 URL、表单或其它信息上附带恶意的XPath "
"查询代码，以获得权限信息的访问权并更改这些信息。XPath注入攻击是针对Web服务应用新的攻击方法，它允许攻击者在事先不知道XPath查询相关知识的情况下，通过XPath查询得到一个XML文档的完整内容。"
msgstr ""
"XPath injection attacks abuse the loose input handling and fault tolerance "
"of XPath parsers by attaching malicious XPath query code to URLs, forms, or "
"other inputs, allowing access to and modification of authorization "
"information. XPath injection is an attack method against web service "
"applications that can allow an attacker to retrieve the complete contents of"
" an XML document through XPath queries without prior knowledge of the "
"related XPath query."

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:9
msgid "Xpath注入攻击原理"
msgstr "How XPath Injection Works"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:10
msgid ""
"XPath注入攻击主要是通过构建特殊的输入，这些输入往往是XPath语法中的一些组合，这些输入将作为参数传入Web "
"应用程序，通过执行XPath查询而执行入侵者想要的操作，下面以登录验证中的模块为例，说明 XPath注入攻击的实现原理。"
msgstr ""
"XPath injection attacks mainly construct special inputs, often combinations "
"of XPath syntax. These inputs are passed as parameters to a web application,"
" and the resulting XPath query executes the attacker's intended operation. "
"The following login verification module illustrates how XPath injection "
"works."

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:12
msgid ""
"在Web 应用程序的登录验证程序中，一般有用户名（username）和密码（password） "
"两个参数，程序会通过用户所提交输入的用户名和密码来执行授权操作。若验证数据存放在XML文件中，其原理是通过查找user表中的用户名 "
"（username）和密码（password）的结果来进行授权访问，"
msgstr ""
"A web application's login verification routine usually has two parameters: "
"username and password. The program performs authorization based on the "
"submitted username and password. If the verification data is stored in an "
"XML file, authorization is performed by looking up the matching username and"
" password in the user table."

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:14
msgid "例存在user.xml文件如下： ::"
msgstr "For example, assume a ``user.xml`` file exists as follows: ::"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:31
msgid ""
"则在XPath中其典型的查询语句为： ``//users/user[loginID/text()='xyz'and "
"password/text()='123test']``"
msgstr ""
"A typical XPath query would be: ``//users/user[loginID/text()='xyz'and "
"password/text()='123test']``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:33
msgid ""
"但是，可以采用如下的方法实施注入攻击，绕过身份验证。如果用 户传入一个 login 和 password，例如 ``loginID = 'xyz' 和 "
"password = '123test'`` ，则该查询语句将返回 true。但如果用户传入类似 ``' or 1=1 or ''='`` "
"的值，那么该查询语句也会得到 true 返回值，因为 XPath "
"查询语句最终会变成如下代码：``//users/user[loginID/text()=''or 1=1 or ''='' and "
"password/text()='' or 1=1 or ''='']``"
msgstr ""
"However, injection can be used to bypass authentication. If the user "
"supplies a login and password such as ``loginID = 'xyz' and password = "
"'123test'``, the query returns true. If the user supplies a value such as "
"``' or 1=1 or ''='``, the query also returns true because the final XPath "
"query becomes: ``//users/user[loginID/text()=''or 1=1 or ''='' and "
"password/text()='' or 1=1 or ''='']``"

#: ../../source/vuln/xpath.rst:35
msgid ""
"这个字符串会在逻辑上使查询一直返回 true 并将一直允许攻击者访问系统。攻击者可以利用 XPath 在应用程序中动态地操作 XML "
"文档。攻击完成登录可以再通过XPath盲入技术获取最高权限帐号和其它重要文档信息。"
msgstr ""
"This string logically causes the query to always return true, allowing the "
"attacker to access the system. The attacker can use XPath to dynamically "
"manipulate XML documents in the application. After logging in, the attacker "
"can further use blind XPath injection to obtain the highest-privileged "
"account and other important document information."
